".........SENTENCE ORDER IN CHINESE.......
subject   time       place     verb    object
  ta    zaoshang zai xuexiao    chi    zaofan
 (He eats breakfast at school in the morning.)"

 :: please, thank you, thank you ::

 thank you (eh) 谢谢 (hp) xièxiè

 qǐng (ph) 请 (he) please
   " (e.g.) qǐng zài zhèlǐ děng  (ph) 请在这里等 (he) please wait here
   " (e.g.) qǐng jìn             (ph) 请进    (he) please enter/come in
   " (e.g.) qǐng kàn yīxià       (ph) 请看一下 (he) please take a look
   " (e.g.) qǐng děng yīxià      (ph) 请等一下 (he) please wait a bit
   " (e.g.) qǐng zuò             (ph) 请坐    (he) please sit

Sūn nǚshì qǐng jìn (ph)  孙女士请进  (he) Ms Sun, please come in
     " (ex) qǐng jìn

 ############################

 :: what people actually say, daily usage ::

 # thank you

 +:: ways to say thank you ::

麻烦你了 (hp) máfan nǐ le (pe) sorry to trouble you = thank you (see) thank you

Nǐ rén zhēn hǎo (ph) 你人真好 (he) You are so kind = thank you  (see) thank you

辛苦你了 (hp) xīnkǔ nǐ le (pe) Thanks a lot/thanks for your hard work = thank you  (see) thank you
多亏有你 (hp) duōkuī yǒu nǐ (pe) many thanks to you = I couldn't have done it without you = thank you  (see) thank you

你帮了我一个大忙 (hp) nǐ bāngle wǒ yīgè dàmáng (pe) You did me a huge favour = thank you  (see) thank you

 -:: ways to say thank you ::

