Chaoshan region (speaks) ***Teochew language also known as Teo-Swa or Chaoshan, or simply "Min". It is a Sino-Tibetan langauge, one of the dialects of Min sometimes incorrectly called ***Hokkien. 

Hokkien (def) The dialect name for the Fujian region of China where the ***Min Language is spoken, adjacent to Taiwan. 

  " (note) Many of the older Chinese texts make more sense in this older tongue, and it remains close to Japanese.

