    " (e.g.) hěnduō niánqīng rén xǐhuān zhège yóuxì (ph) 很多年轻人喜欢这 个游戏 (he) many young people know/like this game 


   ###############

    :: how to say the date ::

  Dates in Chinese follow a big-endian order: Year [年, nián] + Month [月, yuè] + Day [日, rì/号, hào].

 Numbers are read individually, followed by the unit, e.g., 2024 = 二零二四年. Months are numbered 1–12 [一月 to 十二月], and days are numbered 1–31 followed by rì [formal] or hào [spoken]

 4th July (eh) 6月5日 (hp) 4 yuè 7 rì

 19th February 1966 (eh) 一九六六年二月十九号 (hp) yī jiǔ liù liù nián, èr yuè, shí jiǔ hào

 the new year is 2026 (eh)  新年是2026年 (hp) xīnnián shì 2026 nián.


